# Custom Docker images

Homelab custom images are **not** built from this repo. Each image has its own GitHub repository and `Build Image` workflow; CI publishes **bare semver** to GHCR (no `latest` / `main-<sha>`).

| Image | Source repo | GHCR |
|-------|-------------|------|
| hearth | [nerddotdad/hearth](https://github.com/nerddotdad/hearth) | `ghcr.io/nerddotdad/hearth` |
| hearth-sandbox | [nerddotdad/hearth](https://github.com/nerddotdad/hearth) (`sandbox-image/`) | `ghcr.io/nerddotdad/hearth-sandbox` |
| hearth agent sidecar | upstream [nousresearch/hermes-agent](https://hub.docker.com/r/nousresearch/hermes-agent) (pinned in Hearth Deployment) | Docker Hub |

## truecharts (this repo)

- Pin bare semver only: HelmRelease `tag: X.Y.Z` or Deployment `image: ghcr.io/nerddotdad/…:X.Y.Z`.
- Do **not** pin `@sha256` digests for these images (keeps Renovate simple).
- HelmRelease: keep `# renovate: datasource=docker depName=ghcr.io/nerddotdad/…` above `tag:`.
- Deployment: no comment needed — regex custom manager matches the image line.
- Do **not** add Docker sources or image build workflows here.

## Image repos

- Edit `Dockerfile`, sources, and `VERSION` in the dedicated repo.
- `.github/workflows/build-image.yml` bumps patch `VERSION` on push (unless you edited `VERSION` in the commit) and pushes one GHCR tag = that version.
- Manual rebuild: **Actions → Build Image → Run workflow** in the image repo.
